      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "Fix image attachment handling in Control UI chat",
        "body": "## Summary\n\nThis fixes two issues that can cause image attachments from Control UI chat to be lost before they reach the model:\n\n1. `resolveGatewayModelSupportsImages()` could miss image-capable models when the runtime reported a bare model name (for example `gpt-5.4`) while the gateway model catalog stored the provider-qualified id (for example `clipro-codex/gpt-5.4`).\n2. Control UI chat allowed send/Enter to fire while pasted, dropped, or selected attachments were still being loaded through `FileReader`, which could race the attachment state and submit the message before attachments were ready.\n\n## Changes\n\n### Gateway\n- Accept provider-qualified catalog ids when resolving image support.\n- Add a regression test covering `provider/model` catalog ids.\n\n### Control UI\n- Track pending attachment reads in chat state.\n- Increment/decrement the pending counter around `FileReader` usage for paste, file select, and drag/drop.\n- Block Enter/send while attachment reads are still pending.\n- Reset the pending counter on session switch.\n- Add a regression test that verifies chat send is blocked while attachment reads are pending.\n\n## Testing\n\nRan:\n\n```bash\ncorepack pnpm -C /Volumes/ssd/Users/who/.openclaw/workspace/openclaw-upstream test -- --run src/gateway/session-utils.test.ts ui/src/ui/app-chat.test.ts\n```\n\nBoth targeted test suites passed locally.\n",
